==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lisle
<hw>Lisle</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A city of France
celebrated for certain manufactures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lisle glove</b></col>, <cd>a fine summer glove, made of
Lisle thread.</cd> -- <col><b>Lisle lace</b></col>, <cd>a fine handmade
lace, made at Lisle.</cd> -- <col><b>Lisle thread</b></col>, <cd>a hard
twisted cotton thread, originally produced at Lisle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lisne</ent>⟦br⟧
